PySSM

written by Björn Guth at Klinik für Psychiatrie, Psychosomatik und 
Psychotherapie des Kindes- und Jugendalters at Universtitätsklinikum 
Aachen

version 0.3.0

PySSM is a small game to teach children eight syllables needed for a
study on the early symptoms of dyslexia

Dependencies:
    python 2.7 (www.python.org)
    pygame (www.pygame.org)

How to install pyssm?

To install pyssm on linux, go in a shell to the directory with the source code and use the following command:
	python2 setup.py install

To install pyssm on windows, use someting like cmd to go to the directiory with the source code and use the following command:
	setup.py install

or build with
	setup.py bdist_wininst
a .exe or with
	setup.py bdist_msi
a .msi file to install and uninstall it.
